last night.

190
00:07:18,516 --> 00:07:20,283
It totally holds up!

191
00:07:21,786 --> 00:07:25,355
<i>Crocodile Dundee III is the
second-best of the Croc trilogy,</i>

192
00:07:25,356 --> 00:07:28,058
so maybe I can live
with that.

193
00:07:28,059 --> 00:07:29,126
(cell phone beeps)

194
00:07:29,127 --> 00:07:31,795
Oh, sorry,
my phone's charged.

195
00:07:32,597 --> 00:07:35,799
I, uh, I hear you're a woman
who can get things.

196
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,801
I've been known to locate
certain objects

197
00:07:37,802 --> 00:07:38,836
from time to time.

198
00:07:38,837 --> 00:07:42,339
I need vodka
and dirty playing cards.

199
00:07:43,107 --> 00:07:44,741
I got ya.

200
00:07:47,378 --> 00:07:48,912
Oh, my God.

201
00:07:48,913 --> 00:07:50,714
What is it?

202
00:07:50,715 --> 00:07:55,485
I have a voice mail from my dad.

203
00:08:00,988 --> 00:08:02,889
You have a voice mail
from your dad?

204
00:08:02,890 --> 00:08:03,856
How?

205
00:08:03,857 --> 00:08:05,858
My phone's been out of juice,

206
00:08:05,859 --> 00:08:10,880
so he must've called me
the day the he, uh...

207
00:08:10,881 --> 00:08:13,132
Baby, are you okay?

208
00:08:13,133 --> 00:08:19,338
I hold in my hand the last words
my father will ever say to me.

209
00:08:21,241 --> 00:08:23,275
I'm gonna hit play.

210
00:08:25,079 --> 00:08:26,746
What's wrong?

211
00:08:26,747 --> 00:08:30,349
<i>What if it's worse
than Crocodile Dundee III?</i>

212
00:08:31,118 --> 00:08:34,553
I can't do this.
I can't...

213
00:08:34,554 --> 00:08:36,689
My mom is about to collapse.
I'm gonna...

214
00:08:36,690 --> 00:08:39,542
Wait-- no, no, baby...
Baby, I got it. Let me.

215
00:08:42,079 --> 00:08:43,162
You should listen to it.

216
00:08:43,163 --> 00:08:45,031
Just don't put
too much pressure on it.

217
00:08:45,032 --> 00:08:46,249
She's right.

218
00:08:46,250 --> 00:08:48,251
I mean, this idea that
someone's last words have

219
00:08:48,252 --> 00:08:49,602
